
[1]omnisciency

   OMNIS'CIENCY, n. [L. omnis, all, and scientia, knowledge.]

   The quality of knowing all things at once; universal knowledge;
   knowledge unbounded or infinite. Omniscience is an attribute peculiar
   to God.
